HEADWORD: White friar
<hw>White" fri`ar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>A mendicant
monk of the Carmelite order, so called from the white cloaks worn by the
order. See <er>Carmelite</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>White-fronted</ent>⟦br⟧
